# ===========================================
# SUPABASE PROJECT CONFIGURATION
# ===========================================
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your Supabase project values
# cp .env.example .env
#
# HOW TO CONNECT YOUR OWN SUPABASE:
# 1. Create a new Supabase project at https://supabase.com
# 2. Go to Project Settings > API
# 3. Copy the "Project URL" and paste below as VITE_SUPABASE_URL
# 4. Copy the "anon public" key and paste as VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# 5. Copy the "Project Reference ID" (from the URL) as VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID
# 6. Run the SQL files in /supabase-setup/ folder in order (001, 002, 003, 004)
# 7. Run: npm install && npm run dev
# ===========================================

